                            </picture>
                        </div>
                    
                    <div class="col-lg-8 mb-0 mb-lg-2">         
                    <h4>Design was completed and sold to shareholders before <br>delivery team involvement</h4>
                    <p>Being on the delivery side of design, I gained empathy for the developers by noticing how 'concepts' presented to users that aren't vetted from a development standpoint, could cause demos and releases to underwhelm.</p>
                    <p>Design files shown to the client displayed functionality unobtainable in 14 weeks where we had to be strategic in prioritizing features over styling. I addressed the extensive backlog of styling issues to allow additional resources whom could focus on the front-end styling.</p>
                    
                    <h4>UX Advocate for delivery</h4>
                    <p>I led the UI solution on feature execution between design, dev, and stakeholders, such as, feature parity, drag and drop, and annotations. I partnered closely with the design firm and our client to implement a tool called Abstract to better showcase the design files for development since Figma was not allowed.</p>
                    </div>
                    
